Document: CanvasModulate
Path: godot/classes/class_canvasmodulate.rst
Summary: CanvasModulate applies a color tint to all nodes on a canvas and enforces single usage per canvas while allowing CanvasLayer for independent rendering.

CanvasModulate applies a color tint to all nodes on a canvas. Only one can be used to tint a canvas, but CanvasLayer's can be used to render things independently. This node modifies the color of all subsequent nodes in the same canvas layer by multiplying their colors with the CanvasModulate's tint color. The effect is applied to all visible nodes in the canvas layer, including 2D nodes, sprites, and other visual elements. The tint color is specified through the "modulate" property, which accepts a Color value. When multiple CanvasModulate nodes are present in the same canvas, only the last one in the scene tree takes effect. For independent rendering without shared tinting, CanvasLayer nodes can be used to isolate different visual elements into separate layers. This allows for more complex visual effects while maintaining control over individual layers' color modulation. The node does not affect the rendering order or spatial relationships between objects, only the color appearance of all visible nodes in its canvas layer.
